# =============================================================================
# Ticxnova-AI — Environment variables
# =============================================================================

# --- Supabase (client-safe — anon key only) ---
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# --- Stripe Price IDs (public — safe in frontend .env) ---
# Create 3 products in Stripe Dashboard (Starter, Professional, Enterprise).
# Add a recurring monthly price in CAD for each:
#   Starter        → $149 CAD / month
#   Professional   → $499 CAD / month
#   Enterprise     → $999 CAD / month
# Copy each Price ID (starts with price_) below:
#   Ticxnova Starter        → $149 CAD / month  (price_1TezkkH1xnYBWgiRHnzscJTe)
#   Ticxnova Professional   → $499 CAD / month  (price_1TezsyH1xnYBWgiRWJdPkNSn)
#   Ticxnova Enterprise     → $999 CAD / month  (price_1TezwAH1xnYBWgiRaK6gLtRa)

# Test mode price IDs (use with sk_test_ key):
VITE_STRIPE_STARTER_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSG9H1xnYBWgiR8Jrks4o6
VITE_STRIPE_PROFESSIONAL_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSGAH1xnYBWgiRiENaDWTk
VITE_STRIPE_ENTERPRISE_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSGAH1xnYBWgiRkChP3iJc
#
# Live mode price IDs (use with sk_live_ key when going to production):
# VITE_STRIPE_STARTER_PRICE_ID=price_1TezkkH1xnYBWgiRHnzscJTe
# VITE_STRIPE_PROFESSIONAL_PRICE_ID=price_1TezsyH1xnYBWgiRWJdPkNSn
# VITE_STRIPE_ENTERPRISE_PRICE_ID=price_1TezwAH1xnYBWgiRaK6gLtRa

# =============================================================================
# Supabase Edge Function secrets (Dashboard → Project Settings → Edge Functions)
# NEVER put these in the frontend .env or commit real values.
# =============================================================================
#
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx          # Stripe → Developers → API keys
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx        # Stripe → Webhooks → signing secret
#
# Server-side price IDs (test mode — same values as VITE_STRIPE_* above):
# STRIPE_STARTER_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSG9H1xnYBWgiR8Jrks4o6
# STRIPE_PROFESSIONAL_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSGAH1xnYBWgiRiENaDWTk
# STRIPE_ENTERPRISE_PRICE_ID=price_1TrSGAH1xnYBWgiRkChP3iJc
#
# =============================================================================
# Deploy checklist
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Run SQL (Supabase SQL editor, in order):
#    - supabase/saas-maturity.sql
#    - supabase/stripe-billing.sql
#    - supabase/enterprise-hardening.sql
#
# 2. Set edge function secrets (see above), or run:
#    STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx ./scripts/set-stripe-secrets.sh
#
# 3. Deploy functions:
#    supabase functions deploy create-checkout-session
#    supabase functions deploy create-billing-portal-session
#    supabase functions deploy stripe-webhook
#
# 4. Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks → Add endpoint:
#    https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co/functions/v1/stripe-webhook
#    Events: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.*, invoice.paid,
#             invoice.payment_succeeded, invoice.payment_failed
#
# 5. Stripe Dashboard → Settings → Customer portal → enable subscription management.
#
# 6. Restart dev server after changing .env: npm run dev
#
# Flow: User clicks Subscribe → Stripe Checkout → webhook activates subscription.
